Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}(halved and thinly sliced); mince a few slices until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4). Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1}(halved, cored, and sliced into strips). Trim and finely dice @mini cucumber{1}(trimmed and finely diced). Dice @tomato{1}(diced into ¼-inch pieces). Quarter @lemon{1}(quartered).

In a small #pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer.

Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes} (18-20 minutes for 4). Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, toss sliced onion and bell pepper on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, 1 tsp @shawarma spice blend{1%tbsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (You'll use the rest of the Shawarma Spice Blend in the next step.)

Push veggies to one side of #sheet{} (for 4, leave veggies spread out across sheet).

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Place chicken on opposite side of sheet from veggies (for 4 servings, place chicken on a second #baking sheet{}). Rub with a drizzle of oil; season all over with remaining Shawarma Spice Blend, salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack until chicken is cooked through and veggies are tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. (For 4, roast chicken on top rack and veggies on middle rack.)

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine cucumber, tomato, minced onion, ½ tsp @garlic powder{1%tsp} (you'll use more later), and juice from one lemon wedge (1 tsp garlic powder and juice from two lemon wedges for 4 servings).

Add a drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir to combine.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @hummus{4%tbsp}, remaining garlic powder, @olive oil{1%tbsp}, and juice from one lemon wedge (2 TBSP olive oil and juice from two lemon wedges for 4 servings). Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Place @sour cream{3%tbsp} in a separate small bowl. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Slice chicken crosswise.

Serve chicken, rice, veggies, tomato-cuke salad, hummus, crema, @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, and remaining lemon wedges family style.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.